dc_title_s: Structural map on top Judea Group
dc_description_s: Geophysical Institute of Israel. Companion text: Appendix C: Top Judea Group - Digital structural map of Israel / Lorian Fleischer and Rina Gafsou. Geological framework of the Levant. Volume I: Cyprus and Syria. Volume II: The Levantine Basin and Israel / John K. Hall; Valey A. Krasheninnikov; Francis Hirsch; Chaim Benjamini; Akiva Flexer. Jerusalem: Historical Productions-Hall. Vol II. 2005. 745-754 p. North Decimal Degree 33.3333. South Decimal Degree 29.5000. East Decimal Degree 35.8833. West Decimal Degree 32.2000. Map is plate VII. Two maps in one sheet. Map 1) structure is shown by hypsometric tints. Map 2) structure shown by contours. Ancillary map: source map. Verso: "Top Judea key map.".
